of being complimented

00:39:56.040 --> 00:39:58.650
on your looks instead
of your talents.

00:39:58.650 --> 00:40:01.800
I had a colleague toast a
big project, and in front

00:40:01.800 --> 00:40:04.950
of 40 people, comment
on how good I looked

00:40:04.950 --> 00:40:07.090
as well as being
talented on the project.

00:40:07.090 --> 00:40:08.970
And at that moment,
I realized, wow,

00:40:08.970 --> 00:40:11.030
no one would ever say
that to a male colleague.

00:40:11.030 --> 00:40:12.960
You wouldn't say he's
so great at his job,

00:40:12.960 --> 00:40:14.780
and he looks so great.

00:40:14.780 --> 00:40:16.240
You would never hear that.

00:40:16.240 --> 00:40:20.730
So how do you think we
can more proactively model

00:40:20.730 --> 00:40:24.090
emphasizing talents over
looks in the worth of women

00:40:24.090 --> 00:40:24.799
in the workplace?

00:40:24.799 --> 00:40:26.839
GRETCHEN CARLSON: I mean,
again, it starts young.

00:40:26.839 --> 00:40:29.277
Your story reminds me of
Senator Kirsten Gillibrand

00:40:29.277 --> 00:40:30.360
from this state, actually.

00:40:30.360 --> 00:40:31.909
I interviewed her for the book.

00:40:31.909 --> 00:40:33.450
And she was telling
a story about how

00:40:33.450 --> 00:40:36.800
when she was at her law firm
